  <p>
    Dear <%= @user.name.split.first %>,
  </p>

  <p>
    Wow! Thank you for adopting another drain.
  </p>

  <p>
    If you encounter medical waste, construction debris, or if the drain is
    clogged beneath the grate, report non-emergency issues via <a href="https://www.medfordma.org/mayor/online-request-for-city-services/">SeeClickFix</a>  or contact Medford Department of Public Works at 781-393-2417 to have it cleared by the City.
  </p>

  <p>
    As always, please let us know if you have any feedback or questions about
    this program. We love to hear from you.
  </p>

  <p>
    Sincerely,
  </p>
  <p>
    <a href="https://adoptadrain.medford-ma.gov/">Adopt a Drain</a> Team
    <br />
    <a href="tel:781-393-2417">781-393-2417</a>
    <br />
    <a href="mailto:enviro@medford-ma.gov">enviro@medford-ma.gov</a>
  </p>

  <p>
    <em>
      Remember, the City of Medford won't be held responsible for anything that happens to you or others in service of maintaining your drain. Please be careful.
    </em>
  </p>

  <p style="font-style: italic; font-size: 11px;">
    If you move or are no longer able to tend to your drain, please abandon it on
    <a href="https://adopt-a-drain-medford-mass.herokuapp.com/">https://adopt-a-drain-medford-mass.herokuapp.com/</a>. Thank you.
  </p>

